#!/usr/bin/env bash
# =============================================================================
# region Script overview
# =============================================================================
# tracehold
#
# A Bash tool for turning ambiguous field failures into structured,
# timestamped, integrity-conscious engineering case files.
#
# Primary flow:
#   main
#     -> parse_args
#     -> resolve_state
#     -> validate_config
#     -> run_workflow
#
# Early adapters:
#   __complete / --completion bash / --help / --version / --self-test
#
# Tracehold is designed to:
# - preserve evidence before it disappears or is altered;
# - bind logs, configuration, assets, sites, versions, and timestamps together;
# - separate direct observations, known facts, assumptions, and hypotheses;
# - keep original evidence distinct from derived analysis;
# - produce a case another engineer can continue without verbal-only context;
# - connect the eventual finding or fix back to the original field symptom.
#
# Principle:
#   Hold the evidence. Keep the context. Find the truth.
#
# Reading map:
#   S0  Configuration and shared schema
#   S1  Runtime services and diagnostics
#   S2  Core data and validation primitives
#   S3  Command execution and filesystem persistence
#   S4  Runtime state resolution
#   S5  Manifest and report generation
#   S6  CLI contract rendering and help
#   S7  Bash programmable completion
#   S8  Argument parsing
#   S9  Configuration validation
#   S10 Command workflows
#   S11 Self-test
#   S12 Entrypoint

# =============================================================================
# endregion Script overview
# =============================================================================

